By the time he got home, Ning Wangshu was taking his afternoon nap. Zhou Yunsheng tucked him in carefully, kissed his rosy little cheek, and whispered, “I’m sorry for using you. But I will stay by your side and protect you for the rest of my life, until you grow old.”

