Chapter 2.9
The coffee cup brushed past the department head’s face and smashed hard against the office door, producing a loud bang. The shattered porcelain left deep scratches on the expensive furniture. The department head stood frozen in place, stunned. It took him several seconds to finally lift a trembling hand to wipe the cold sweat off his forehead. In a shaky voice, he asked, "B-boss, is there something wrong with the proposal?"

Even if there were issues, there was no reason to be this furious—he looked as if someone had just killed his entire family.

Ning Sinian stared at the computer screen, his face dark as thunder, his chest heaving violently. He was clearly on the verge of exploding.

He cast a cold glance at the department head and waved his hand dismissively. As if granted amnesty, the department head dashed out of the office at once.

On the computer screen, the young man was brushing his teeth. This was already the fifth time, and the foam he spat out was tinged with blood. Ning Sinian could almost taste the metallic bitterness on his own tongue—he was seething with rage.

He wished he could tear Zhao Xinfang apart.

But not yet. He had just thrown out some bait for Qian Yu, who was now on his way to the Ning residence.

He was about to call Zhao Jun to stop the young man—if he kept brushing like this, his gums would start rotting. But just as he picked up the phone, he saw his sleepy-eyed son shuffling toward the young man in oversized slippers.

"Uncle, let's go paint," the boy said, tugging at the young man's pant leg.

Despite feeling miserable, the young man quickly composed himself, spat out the foam, wiped his mouth, and pretended as if nothing had happened. He held the boy’s hand and led him to the art studio. But his mind was clearly elsewhere—he stood in front of the easel for a long time without making a single stroke.

Ning Sinian stared at him, his eyes dry and bloodshot from the intensity of his gaze. He finally squeezed his eyes shut and gritted out a name between clenched teeth—Zhao. Xin. Fang. How dare you?!

With his employer breathing down his neck, Qian Yu was desperate to get his hands on the bidding documents. The moment he stepped into the Ning residence, he was forcefully shoved into the study. The door slammed shut behind him, and a warm body pressed up against his.

Qian Yu was momentarily surprised, but quickly turned the tables, taking full control of the situation. After an intense session on the couch, Zhao Xinfang tried to drag him to the desk for another round, but he refused.

"Why are you so desperate? Ning Sinian not satisfying you?" Qian Yu smirked, adjusting his clothes. "We can't keep going. If we take too long, someone might catch us."

"He hasn't touched me in months," Zhao Xinfang grumbled, her expression dark. "Does he have someone else? Who is it?"

"Never heard anything," Qian Yu said indifferently. "Maybe your charm just wore off."

"So be it. He only married me to bear his child anyway. He might as well have just hired a nanny."

"A nanny wouldn’t be as beautiful as you. Wouldn't have your body. Wouldn't be as wild as you."

